      "role": "user",
      "content": "<|channel>thought\n<channel|>That makes sense. I think the issue might be that some data packets are being dropped or arriving late, so the list length isn't what I expect it to be. Actually, I'm working on a larger climate simulation project right now, and I've noticed some huge, unexplained spikes in the temperature data that don't match our historical models. It's almost like the data is oscillating wildly for no reason. Do you think that's just a sensor error or something in the simulation logic?",
